    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.5.15" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">15</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">DAVID STARR JORDAN
                        <lb/>
                    STANFORD UNIVERSITY
                        <lb/>
                    CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 25th, 1918.</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John N<del><unclear>z</unclear>e</del><add>ei</add>hardt,</addrLine>
                
                        <addrLine>Bancroft, Nebraska.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. N<del>ie</del><add>ei</add>hardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Let me thank you for your beautiful letter. I am glad that you had a pleasant visit with us and such a charming episode on your way back. Some day we will admit you to the Stanford ring also.</p>
                
                <p>I shall be delighted to visit you if I come to your part of the country. I must make my visit pay my way. Maybe the folks at Wayne and some other of the schools or colleges may want to be told more about the interior of Prussia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With best wishes, I am,</salute>
                    <salute>Very sincerely yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>David Starr Jordan</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
